  "description": "ngen.exe is the .NET Native Image Generator, which precompiles .NET assemblies to native code for faster startup. It runs as part of .NET servicing. Attackers abuse the scheduled tasks and execution paths around it to run code through a signed Microsoft binary.\n",
  "about": "ngen.exe compiles managed assemblies into native images and maintains those images, work normally driven by .NET setup and by the \".NET Framework NGEN\" scheduled tasks that run during idle time. It ships with the .NET Framework, so the genuine binary lives under `C:\\Windows\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework` and `Framework64`, not `System32`.\n\nLegitimately, ngen runs automatically after .NET updates and during maintenance windows, parented by the Task Scheduler. Interactive or oddly-parented invocations are what give an instance meaning.\n",
